column1: Who will win the 2020 Golden Globe for Best Performance by an Actor in a Motion Picture - Musical or Comedy?
column5: ['Daniel Craig (Knives Out)', 'Roman Griffin Davis (Jojo Rabbit)', 'Leonardo DiCaprio (Once Upon a Time...in Hollywood)', 'Taron Egerton (Rocketman)', 'Eddie Murphy (Dolemite Is My Name)', 'A tie or other outcome']

column6: Eddie Murphy's return got a lot of attention and positive reviews. DiCaprio was outstanding, but Murphy has a slight edge. Craig would be the dark-horse choice for an unusual comic role.
